						<div class="title-line" id="method">Safety Issues</div>
						<h5>How did we address the safety issues in our project?</h5>
						<ul><li>A <b>non-pathogenic chassis</b>, i.e. <i>E.coli DH5α</i>, <i>E.coli BL21</i> (DE3), is chosen.</li>
								<li>The chassis is in small <b>enclosed space</b> as a barrier to prevent contamination.</li>
								<li><b>"Suicide-gene inducers"</b> in the enclosed space are designed to kill <i>E.coli</i> in the bio-sensing strip.</li>
						</ul>
						<div class="title-line" id="plan">Safety Plan</div>
						<p>Our  <i>E.coli</i> can sense urea glucose. When the glucose level is high, the bacteria can express red fluorescent protein (RFP) as a reporter to give a signal which can be detected using excitation. After the detection, the “suicide-gene inducers”, arabinose, induce the P<sub>BAD</sub> promoter (<a href="http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K206000">BBa_K206000</a>) and then activate the transcription of the lysis gene (<a href="http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K117000">BBa_K117000</a>). The functional assays are showed in <a href="{{projResults}}#safety">Bio-Safety System (PROJECT / Results)</a>.</p>
