						<h5>Building a safe lab</h5>
						<p>We operated the project in the Biosafety Level 1 (BSL-1) Lab. The space is suitable for experiments in all of our chassis which are Risk Group 1 organisms. Additionally, we always handled biological materials in a laminar flow hood. All of biowastes were autoclaved at the typical 121 °C/15 psi for 15 minutes.</p>

						<div class="title-line" id="law">Laws and Regulations</div>
						<h5>Obeying the laws and regulations of biosafety in our Country/ University</h5>
						<p>Regarding the Environmental Protection, Safety and Health Center is responsible for the safety of biology labs at National Cheng Kung University (<a href="{{ref3}}" target="_blank">Guidelines for Laboratory Biosafety</a>). And Centers for Disease Control (CDC) is the department to govern biosafety for research laboratories in our country (<a href="{{ref4}}" target="_blank">Laboratory Biosafety Management: A Compilation of Regulations and Administrative Guidance</a>).</p>
